<h1>Problem 2120 - 2019 Singapore TST Day 1, P3 of 3, N</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 8</h2>
<p>Let \(n\) be a natural number. A sequence is \(k-\)complete if it contains all residues modulo \(n^k\). Let \(Q(x)\) be a polynomial with integer coefficients. For \(k\ge 2\), define \(Q^k(x)=Q(Q^{k-1}(x))\), where \(Q^1(x)=Q(x)\). Show that if \[0,Q(0),Q^2(0),Q^3(0),\ldots\]is \(2018-\)complete, then it is \(k-\)complete for all positive integers \(k\).</p>
